      "amount": "to taste"
    },
    {
      "name": "Paprika",
      "amount": "1/4 tsp"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "In a small pan, heat the spicy tadka oil over medium heat.",
    "Add the crushed bay leaves and cook for 1-2 minutes, until fragrant.",
    "In a large bowl, combine the tuna, lemon juice, olive oil, red onion, parsley, dill, garlic, salt, black pepper, and paprika.",
    "Stir well to combine.",
    "Add the cooked bay leaves to the tuna mixture and stir gently.",
    "Taste and adjust the seasoning as needed.",
    "Cover and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes to allow the flavors to meld.",
    "Just before serving, stir in the spicy tadka oil.",
    "Serve chilled or at room temperature."
